reviewText: I didn't really like the first two seasons, and the third was marginal, but this one was pretty good.Quinn, my favorite character, gets a larger share of the stories, and is better written as a more three-dimensional person than she has been previously. At last, she is more that a cardboard caricature of a geeky genius. She is why I give this season four stars.The rest of the actors are their usual mediocre,  predictable selves.
summary: Probably the best season, saved by Quinn.

reviewText: Unfortunately the finale episode PCA Confidential isn't included on this set (no idea why). Some reviews have said it's on Season 3, but on my version it wasn't. It may only be included on the Canadian version. It only plays in Region 1 DVD players. I own a Sony and it plays just fine. You should be getting 3 discs in your set.DISC ONETrading Places- Zoey returns to PCA and Chase transfers to Covington- without the other knowing itFake Roommate- Logan and Michael try to convince the housing lady that Chase still lives with them to avoid getting a new roommateAlone At PCA- Logan and Michael are accused of breaking Dean Rivers's prized statueRumor of Love- There is a rumor going around PCA that Zoey and James are datingDISC TWOAnger Management- Logan is forced to take anger management classesQuinn Misses the Mark- Quinn tries to get Mark back after they break upWalk-A-Thon- Lola owes more money for a walk-a-thon than she originally thought she pledgedVince Is Back- Vince Blake is back to show he's changedDISC THREEDinner For Too Many- Quinn and Logan want an evening alone, but their dinner is ruined when Zoey and her friends crash the partyCoffee Cart Ban- Zoey and her friends secretly set up coffee bars in their dorms after coffee is banned from PCARollercoaster- Zoey tries to help Michael get over his fear of roller coastersChasing Zoey: Part One- Zoey and her friends get ready for the promChasing Zoey: Part TwoNo bonus featuresI think this season is one of the weakest of the Zoey series, but if you're a real fan, I recommend getting it to complete your collection. I was able to get it for $15.29 which is a good price. But if you want the PCA Confidential episode, maybe try looking for a different version of the disc.
